This paper is about a machine learning model for named entity disambiguation in natural language processing. The paper discusses the use of gradient tree boosting, a widely used machine learning algorithm, for structured learning in language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of global features and inference algorithms, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and classification, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
